OL,3,C'We are still waiting for justice':
OL,4,CInfected blood victims call on PM to
OL,5,Cact
OL,7,FCampaigners handed their letter in to
OL,8,F10 Downing Street on the anniversary
OL,9,Fof the seminal report into the scandal.
OL,11,FThe Infected Blood Inquiry concluded
OL,12,Fthat the scandal "could largely have
OL,13,Fbeen avoided" and there was a
OL,14,F"pervasive" cover-up to hide the truth.
OL,16,FMore than 30,000 people in the UK were
OL,17,Finfected with HIV and hepatitis C
OL,18,Fafter they were given contaminated
OL,19,Fblood and blood products between the
OL,20,F1970s and early 1990s.
